\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Manifold: 
\series default
 A set of points with well-understood connectedness property. How we connect on region of space time into another region.(For More rigorous discussion insight please refer Carrol Book on General Relativity.) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Space?????: 
\series default
 Event When and where something happens. Essentially event is fundamental notion of a coordinate in space and time . 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Labels:
\series default
 i.e coordinates we attach to events,but the event itself is independent on the choice of coordinate system or labels. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Metric:
\series default
 A notion of distance between events in manifold. Without this, manifold has no notion of distance encoded in it. The idea that the mathematical structure that tells me how far apart the two events are is intimately connected to the properties of gravity. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Special Relativity:
\series default
 Simplest theory of spacetime, corresponds to general relativity where there is no gravity. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Inertial Reference Frame:
\series default
 A lattice of clocks and measuring rods that allows us to label-assign coordinates to spacetime events. (
\shape italic
refer to the book of S Thorne on Gravitation
\shape default
) Is at rest with respect to someone who does not feel any force acting on it.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 Properties in respect of Inertial Frame of Reference: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
This lattice moves freely through spacetime, No force acting in it, is not rotating. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Measuring rods are orthogonal wrt each other. i.e. orthogonal coordinate system. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Spacing system of measurement are uniformly ticked. Tick mark are uniformly spaced. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
clocks tick uniformly 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Clock Synchronized using 
\series bold

